    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Global Cooperation</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Thomas Crowley letter on Oct 29 article deplores Bush administration's failure to take part in international meeting on climate change</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''U.S. Is Taking a Back Seat in Latest Talks on Climate'' (news article, Oct. 29):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''U.S. Is Taking a Back Seat in Latest Talks on Climate'' (news article, Oct. 29):</p>
        <p>It is ironic that the Bush administration's position on the sidelines of the 150-country Kyoto Protocol meeting in Morocco comes at the same time that the United States is making great efforts to draw other countries into a multilateral action to fight terrorism. Our justifications for cooperation on terrorism are undermined by our own actions involving cooperation on the environment.</p>
        <p>THOMAS CROWLEY  Chapel Hill, N.C., Oct. 29, 2001</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
